<HL>
   Air Wis Traffic Up 18%
</HL>
<DATE>
09/19/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   ARWS
</CO>
<IN>
AIRLINES (AIR)
</IN>
<LP>
   APPLETON, Wis. -- Air Wis Services said its August traffic
rose 18% to 48.7 million revenue passenger miles from 41.3
million miles a year earlier.
   A revenue passenger mile is one paying passenger flown one
mile.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Air Wis Services' results include the company's Air
Wisconsin and Aspen Airways units. The company, which
operates as a commuter carrier for UAL Corp.'s United
Airlines unit, said Aspen results aren't included in the
year-ago period.
   For the first eight months of the year, Air Wis traffic
rose 9.8% to 319.2 million revenue passenger miles from 290.7
million miles a year ago.
   August load factor, or percentage of seats filled, rose to
52.5% from 50.5% a year ago. For the year to date, load
factor slipped to 45.7% from 47.7%.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
