<HL>
   Swiss Trade Deficit Widens
</HL>
<DATE>
09/19/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<IN>
MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)
</IN>
<LP>
   BERN -- Switzerland's trade deficit widened in August to
1.03 billion Swiss francs ($806 million) from a revised gap
of 580.1 million francs in July, the government reported.
   In August 1989, the trade deficit was 1.43 billion francs.
</LP>
