   Financing Business:
   Anadarko Petroleum
</HL>
<DATE>
09/19/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   APC
</CO>
<IN>
OIL, SECONDARY (OIS)
PETROLEUM (PET)
BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
</IN>
<LP>
   ANADARKO PETROLEUM (Houston) -- said it will redeem on
Oct. 18, the entire $100 million principal amount outstanding
of its 5 3/4% convertible subordinated debentures, due 2012.
Under the exchange offer, holders will receive $1,042.97,
which includes an early call premium and accrued interest,
for each $1,000 principal amount of debentures held. Or, the
company said, holders may opt to convert the debentures into
Anadarko common at a conversion price of $32.625 a share.
Anadarko, an oil and gas exploration and production concern,
said a conversion into common of the debentures would reduce
debt by about $100 million, from a level of about $474
million at June 30, and increase the number of shares
outstanding by 5.8% or roughly 3.1 million shares. Anadarko
has about 52.4 million shares currently outstanding.
</LP>
