<HL>
   New Jersey Power Outage
   Affects Telerate Service
</HL>
<DATE>
09/19/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C11
</SO>
<CO>
   DJ
</CO>
<IN>
MEDIA, PUBLISHING, BROADCASTING, ELECTRONIC PUBLISHING (MED)
ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- Telerate Inc.'s financial information service
was stopped for more than two hours yesterday due to a power
outage at its main computer operation in Jersey City, N.J.
   Telerate service was knocked out at around 7:15 a.m. EDT
because of an explosion at a Public Service Electric &amp; Gas
Co. facility that serves the Telerate building in Jersey
City, according to a spokesman for Dow Jones &amp; Co., which
owns Telerate.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The outage affected Telerate's news and market commentary
subscribers, who couldn't access the information services.
Telerate's foreign exchange trading services weren't
affected.
   The Dow Jones spokesman, who said Telerate's services have
returned to normal, said he didn't expect any further
complications.
   Telerate provides live quotes of U.S. government
securities and other debt instruments, futures prices and
additional financial data, as well as other news and
information.
