<HL>
   International Brief -- Cie. de Saint-Gobain:
   Firm Seeks Approval to Lift
   Its Stake in Oberland Glas
</HL>
<DATE>
09/19/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A18
</SO>
<CO>
   F.STG G.OLG
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
BUILDING MATERIALS (BLD)
</IN>
<LP>
   Cie. de Saint-Gobain said it applied for regulatory
approval to raise its holdings in the West German glass group
Oberland Glas AG above 50%, from the current level of 35%.
   A spokesman for the French glass and building-materials
group said, however, that the move is preliminary at this
stage and might not lead to an actual increase in its stake
until 1991 or 1992.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Saint-Gobain acquired its stake in Oberland in 1988
through a share swap with the Wiegand family, which retains a
25% interest. The French company has first refusal rights on
that 25% block, and would need prior regulatory approval
before it could exercise them.
   Oberland couldn't immediately be reached for comment.
</TEXT>
