<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
DIVERSIFIED MINING (MNG)
</IN>
<LP>
   Societe Generale de Belgique, Belgium's largest holding
company, is facing a difficult period as a string of units
are expected to report disappointing first-half earnings.
   The Belgium holding company's recently restructured
minings and metals unit, Acec-Union Miniere, reported
first-half net income of 3.7 billion Belgian francs ($116.1
million). Analysts estimate that a year-earlier figure would
have been about 6.3 billion Belgian francs.
